The paper deals with analytical results related to wireless communications, specifically the performance evaluation of digital communications over fading channels and the information-theoretic analysis of multiple-input multiple-output systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves the derivation of upper and lower bounds, which suggests the possibility of numerical analysis, making cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) another likely category. The use of closed-form expressions and the study of functions and integrals suggest cs.SI (Systems and Control) and cs.MS (Mathematical Software) as possible categories. Finally, the study of wireless communication systems and fading channels suggests cs.SP (Signal Processing) as a possible category.
